name: Mount Kearsarge (Warner)

trails_config.name: Winslow & Barlow Loop
trails_config.description: A favorite family hike: from Winslow State Park, ascend the steep but short Winslow Trail 1.1 miles to the summit, where a historic fire tower provides 360° views spanning from the Whites to Vermont’s peaks. Descend via the gentler Barlow Trail to complete the loop. This well-maintained loop is full of rewards for little effort and is a perfect introduction to hiking New Hampshire’s mountains.
trails_config.parking_info: Winslow State Park, Kearsarge Mountain Rd

current_conditions.ai_summary: Experience the beauty of New Hampshire on Mount Kearsarge (Warner). At 2930 feet, this summit commands impressive views of the surrounding wilderness.
risk_factors: Check local trail conditions before departing.
Start early to avoid afternoon storms.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 2930 feet, Mount Kearsarge (Warner) is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Winslow & Barlow Loop**, a **2.8 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **local peak challenge**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

This peak stands relatively isolated, offering a solitary summit experience.
